17. [출제의도] 대화의 특정 정보 파악하기
M: Is there anything I can do for you, ma’am?
W: Well, I want to buy a new smartphone.
M: Do you have any special brand in mind?
W: No. I can’t decide which one to buy.
M: Then, let me help you. Look at this chart.  
I think a screen size over 5 inches is 
inconvenient to carry.
W: Yeah, I want a convenient one.
M: Okay. How about pixels? If you want quality 
photos, you need high pixels.
W: Pixels are not that important to me. 
M: Then, what price range do you want?
W: It should be less than $200.
M: Okay, ma’am. Now you have only two options.
W: I’ll take the cheaper one.
