dog. 
M: Really? I thought you didn’t like dogs.
W: I don’t. But my children want to have a dog. 
If I take your puppy, they’ll be very excited.
M: Thanks. Your children and my dog Jerry will 
be very happy together.
W: I hope so. And I’m thinking of letting my 
children take care of the dog all by 
themselves.
M: That’s a good idea. While looking after him, 
they’ll be able to learn the responsibility 
needed for keeping a pet.
W:                                         
